node.text: Introducing, “Hurricanes: Uncharted” – a new documentary series from New Jersey surfer/filmmaker duo @robkellysurf and @rsmallcheck, partnered up with Surfline’s forecast team, as they chase down swells on the East Coast in what’s shaping up to be an historic 2021 season. “There’s so much that goes on with these swells,” says Simalchick, “and the level of dedication that these people put into surfing is truly something worth capturing.” Hit the link in bio to read more about project.

🎥: @peterkingphoto

node.text:
True: the West Coast just enjoyed a(nother) great run of Southern Hemi from back-to-back storms that pushed through the central South Pacific last week. Here's how: "These storms took favorable tracks, were large and intense with peak seas north of 40 feet," said Director of Forecasting, Kevin Wallis (@kwallissurfline). "They had strong high pressure support on their northwest flanks, and moved over an already excited sea state from previous storms (the oven was 'preheated'). Not only was there solid size, but also good consistency with lots of waves in the sets." And yeah: the pictures tell the rest of the story.
📷: @miahklein

node.text:
Hurricane Bill (2009) is the benchmark for many East Coast surfers when it comes to tropical storms. How did Larry stack up? It was almost as perfect. The long interval swells overloaded some regions with closeouts and river-like rip currents. The place to be for Larry was in the Northeast, where the surf pumped relentlessly. The region's points, slabs, and sand-bottom novelties gifted locals unforgettable rides they'll be recounting for years to come. Relive Hurricane Larry at the link in our bio. #ChasingHurricaneLarry #swellstory 

📷: @iandeveau, @fullnelson_photo, @nevinsphoto, @jerseymike, @tlagrega

node.text:
We gather here today to pay tribute to one hell of a hurricane swell. Hurricane Larry was born in the Caribbean and spent its life traveling. Larry first visited Puerto Rico and kissed its reefs with azure tubes. Larry sauntered up America's east coast. Florida to Nova Scotia felt Larry's love. Larry wasn't done yet. Larry crossed the Atlantic to the shores of Europe, where it will be forever memorialized by a #SwellStory now playing on our site. Hurricane Larry journeyed over 2,000 nautical miles before coming to rest off the west coast of Africa. Larry, you will be missed. #ChasingHurricaneLarry 
📷: Zurf Collection | @malsurf | @clarejamesphotography | @_rtshots | @tobybutlerphoto

2021 has been the “Year of the Local” in Australia — and many other regions isolated by lockdowns to their regional bubbles. New South Wales was blessed last week with a multiple-day run of swell. Photographer Zach Bowden’s phone lit up like a Christmas tree with people freaking out at how good it was. “Monday saw my local beachie go the best I’ve ever seen it. I got there kinda late, not expecting it to be anything too special -- I was gobsmacked to see perfect six-foot reeling tubes down the beach.” Hit the link in bio for a new #SwellStory from the NSW South Coast.
